  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>\"Fear. That is what we live with. And we live it every day. Only in death are we free of it.\"</em></p><h5 id=\"benefit\">Benefit</h5><p>Fear isn't necessarily a bad thing. It saves lives. The first time you are faced with an attack or jutsu that would reduce your hp to 0 per short rest, you add +2 to your AC and all saving throws until the start of your next turn. Additionally, once per long rest you may grant an attack aimed at you disadvantage as you unpredictably begin to cry and beg.</p><h5 id=\"negative\">Negative</h5><p>You have disadvantage against gaining the first rank of Fear.</p>",
